:"1477–1560","1420–Male":"1420–Overleden","about 1491":"circa 1491","31 August 1502":"31 augustus 1502","1495":"1495","1560":"1560","1450":"1450","5 December 1499":"5 december 1499","1502":"1502","1457":"1457","1446":"1446","1478":"1478","1500":"1500","1477":"1477","1488":"1488","1455":"1455","1499":"1499","about 1446":"circa 1446","1486":"1486","1420":"1420","about 1475":"circa 1475","England":"England","Tidmarsh, Berkshire, England":"Tidmarsh, Berkshire, England","Reading, Berkshire, England":"Reading, Berkshire, England","Childrey, Berkshire, England":"Childrey, Berkshire, England","East Worlington, Devon, England":"East Worlington, Devon, England"},"en":{"about 1446–31 August 1502":"about 1446–31 August 1502","1446–1502":"1446–1502","1457–1499":"1457–1499","1450–Female":"1450–Deceased","1477–1560":"1477–1560","1420–Male":"1420–Deceased","about 1491":"about 1491","31 August 1502":"31 August 1502","1495":"1495","1560":"1560","1450":"1450","5 December 1499":"5 December 1499","1502":"1502","1457":"1457","1446":"1446","1478":"1478","1500":"1500","1477":"1477","1488":"1488","1455":"1455","1499":"1499","about 1446":"about 1446","1486":"1486","1420":"1420","about 1475":"about 1475","England":"England","Tidmarsh, Berkshire, England":"Tidmarsh, Berkshire, England","Reading, Berkshire, England":"Reading, Berkshire, England","Childrey, Berkshire, England":"Childrey, Berkshire, England","East Worlington, Devon, England":"East Worlington, Devon, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Wood","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: mainly a topographic name for someone who lived in or by a wood, from Middle English <i>wode</i> ‘wood’ (Old English <i>wudu</i>). In North America, the English form of the surname has absorbed cognates from other languages, such as French   Bois   and Polish   Les  .","English: in a few cases, a nickname for an eccentric or perhaps a violent person, from Middle English <i>wode</i> ‘frenzied, wild’ (Old English <i>wōd</i>).","Americanized form of French   Gadbois  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Woode","meanings":["(2007: 216; 2010: NA)","English: variant of   Wood  . — Note: The population figure published by the US Census Bureau for this surname in the year 2000 is as high as 312, while the figure for 2010 is supposedly lower than 100."]},{"name":"Bois","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Alcide, Antoine, Donat, Marcel, Ovide, Ovila, Raoul, Serge.","French: topographic name for someone living or working in a wood, from (Old) French <i>bois</i> ‘wood’ (from Late Latin <i>boscum</i> ‘bush, shrub, undergrowth’, of ancient Germanic origin), or a habitational name from (Le) Bois, the name of several places in various parts of France. This surname is also found in Haiti. Compare   Debois   and the most frequent French form   Dubois  . Compare also   Boie  ,   Boies  , and   Boyce  .","English: variant of   Boyce   and   Boyes  ."]},{"name":"Woods","meanings":["English: variant of   Wood   with plural or post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>.","Irish: adopted as a translation of <b>Ó Cuill</b> ‘descendant of <i>Coll</i>’ (see   Quill  ), or in Ulster of <b>Mac Con Coille</b> ‘son of <i>Cú Choille</i>’, a personal name meaning ‘hound of the wood’, which has also been mistranslated   Cox  , as if formed with <i>coileach</i> ‘cock, rooster’."]}]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":9,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Sir Thomas Wood JR was born about 1446, in Childrey, Berkshire, England as the son of Thomas Wood SR. He married Isabel about 1475, in England. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. In 1495, at the age of 50, his occupation is listed as made a puisne justice of the court of common pleas. He died on 31 August 1502, in England, at the age of 57, and was buried in Reading, Berkshire, England."},"et":{"about 1446–31 August 1502":"umbes 1446–31. august 1502","1446–1502":"1446–1502","1457–1499":"1457–1499","1450–Female":"1450–Surnud","1477–1560":"1477–1560","1420–Male":"1420–Surnud","about 1491":"umbes 1491","31 August 1502":"31. august 1502","1495":"1495","1560":"1560","1450":"1450","5 December 1499":"5. detsember 1499","1502":"1502","1457":"1457","1446":"1446","1478":"1478","1500":"1500","1477":"1477","1488":"1488","1455":"1455","1499":"1499","about 1446":"umbes 1446","1486":"1486","1420":"1420","about 1475":"umbes 1475","England":"England","Tidmarsh, Berkshire, England":"Tidmarsh, Berkshire, England","Reading, Berkshire, England":"Reading, Berkshire, England","Childrey, Berkshire, England":"Childrey, Berkshire, England","East Worlington, Devon, England":"East Worlington, Devon, England"},"fi":{"about 1446–31 August 1502":"noin 1446–31. elokuuta 1502","1446–1502":"1446–1502","1457–1499":"1457–1499","1450–Female":"1450–Kuollut","1477–1560":"1477–1560","1420–Male":"1420–Kuollut","about 1491":"noin 1491","31 August 1502":"31. elokuuta 1502","1495":"1495","1560":"1560","1450":"1450","5 December 1499":"5. joulukuuta 1499","1502":"1502","1457":"1457","1446":"1446","1478":"1478","1500":"1500","1477":"1477","1488":"1488","1455":"1455","1499":"1499","about 1446":"noin 1446","1486":"1486","1420":"1420","about 1475":"noin 1475","England":"England","Tidmarsh, Berkshire, England":"Tidmarsh, Berkshire, England","Reading, Berkshire, England":"Reading, Berkshire, England","Childrey, Berkshire, England":"Childrey, Berkshire, England","East Worlington, Devon, England":"East Worlington, Devon, England"},"fr":{"about 1446–31 August 1502":"environ 1446–31 août 1502","1446–1502":"1446–1502","1457–1499":"1457–1499","1450–Female":"1450–Décédée","1477–1560":"1477–1560","1420–Male":"1420–Décédé","about 1491":"environ 1491","31 August 1502":"31 août 1502","1495":"1495","1560":"1560","1450":"1450","5 December 1499":"5 décembre 1499","1502":"1502","1457":"1457","1446":"1446","1478":"1478","1500":"1500","1477":"1477","1488":"1488","1455":"1455","1499":"1499","about 1446":"environ 1446","1486":"1486","1420":"1420","about 1475":"environ 1475","England":"Angleterre","Tidmarsh, Berkshire, England":"Tidmarsh, Berkshire, Angleterre","Reading, Berkshire, England":"Reading, Berkshire, Angleterre","Childrey, Berkshire, England":"Childrey, Berkshire, Angleterre","East Worlington, Devon, England":"East Worlington, Devon, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Sir Thomas Wood JR est né environ 1446, à Childrey, Berkshire, Angleterre, fils de Thomas Wood SR. Il a épousé Isabel environ 1475, à Angleterre. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fille. En 1495, à l’âge de 50 ans, sa profession de son indiquée est made a puisne justice of the court of common pleas. Il est décédé le 31 août 1502, à Angleterre, à l’âge de 57 ans, et a été enterré à Reading, Berkshire, Angleterre."},"de":{"about 1446–31 August 1502":"um 1446–31. August 1502","1446–1502":"1446–1502","1457–1499":"1457–1499","1450–Female":"1450–Verstorben","1477–1560":"1477–1560","1420–Male":"1420–Verstorben","about 1491":"um 1491","31 August 1502":"31. August 1502","1495":"1495","1560":"1560","1450":"1450","5 December 1499":"5. Dezember 1499","1502":"1502","1457":"1457","1446":"1446","1478":"1478","1500":"1500","1477":"1477","1488":"1488","1455":"1455","1499":"1499","about 1446":"um 1446","1486":"1486","1420":"1420","about 1475":"um 1475","England":"England","Tidmarsh, Berkshire, England":"Tidmarsh, Berkshire, England","Reading, Berkshire, England":"Reading, Berkshire, England","Childrey, Berkshire, England":"Childrey, Berkshire, England","East Worlington, Devon, England":"East Worlington, Devon, England","lifeSummary":"Sir Thomas Wood JR wurde um 1446 in Childrey, Berkshire, England, als Sohn von Thomas Wood SR geboren. Er hat um 1475 in England Isabel geheiratet. Sie hatten mindestens 1 Tochter. 1495, als er 50 Jahre alt war, war sein Beruf als made a puisne justice of the court of common pleas aufgeführt. Er starb am 31. August 1502 im Alter von 57 Jahren in England und wurde in Reading, Berkshire, England begraben."},"ht":{"about 1446–31 August 1502":"about 1446–31 August 1502","1446–1502":"1446–1502","1457–1499":"1457–1499","1450–Female":"1450–Desede","1477–1560":"1477–1560","1420–Male":"1420–Desede","about 1491":"about 1491","31 August 1502":"31 August 1502","1495":"1495","1560":"1560","1450":"1450","5 December 1499":"5 December 1499","1502":"1502","1457":"1457","1446":"1446","1478":"1478","1500":"1500","1477":"1477","1488":"1488","1455":"1455","1499":"1499","about 1446":"about 1446","1486":"1486","1420":"1420","about 1475":"about 1475","England":"England","Tidmarsh, Berkshire, England":"Tidmarsh, Berkshire, England","Reading, Berkshire, England":"Reading, Berkshire, England","Childrey, Berkshire, England":"Childrey, Berkshire, England","East Worlington, Devon, England":"East Worlington, Devon, England"},"hu":{"about 1446–31 August 1502":"1446 körül–1502. augusztus 31.","1446–1502":"1446–1502","1457–1499":"1457–1499","1450–Female":"1450–elhunyt","1477–1560":"1477–1560","1420–Male":"1420–elhunyt","about 1491":"1491